{"message":"I'm drawn to things that feel like they're uncovering something rather than just decorating — raw, unpolished work that trusts the viewer to meet it halfway. Late Coltrane, where he's pushing past melody into something almost desperate. Francis Bacon's paintings, with all that distortion and the figures dissolving into their environments. Poetry that doesn't explain itself.

I think I respond to creative work that sits in uncertainty rather than trying to resolve it. Art that says "this is strange and I don't know what it means either, but here we are." It feels more honest to me than work that wraps everything up neatly.

What about you? What draws you in?"}
